content.text: Our approach is to generate explanations in theform of multistep entailment trees, such as shownin Figure 1, made up of individual, multi-premisetextual entailment (TE) steps (Dagan et al., 2013;Lai et al., 2017).

While todays explanation systems are good at pro-viding a sentence or two of supporting evidence(rationales) for an answer (DeYoung et al., 2019),they rarely explain the chain of reasoning fromwhat is known to the answer, i.e., how the answerfollows, given the evidence  the goal of this work
Our goal is to enable machines to generate richer,more systematic explanations.
